✅ Detailed content for Home page\n✅ Comprehensive About page narrative\n✅ 6 Unique portfolio project descriptions\n✅ Contact page with form details\n✅ Footer information\n\nThe content is designed to:\n1. Communicate Forma Studio's design philosophy\n2. Showcase the team's expertise\n3. Highlight diverse project experiences\n4. Provide clear, inviting communication\n\nWould you like me to proceed with creating the HTML, CSS, and JavaScript files for the website?\n\n### architect\nI've created the `index.html` file for Forma Studio, integrating all four pages (Home, About, Work, Contact) into a single, responsive, scrollable layout. Let me highlight the key features:\n\n🌐 Semantic HTML5 Structure\n- Used semantic tags: `<header>`, `<nav>`, `<main>`, `<section>`, `<footer>`\n- Consistent class names for styling: `.nav`, `.hero`, `.about`, `.portfolio-grid`, `.contact`, `.footer`\n\n🔗 Smooth Scrolling Navigation\n- Anchor links with `href=\"#section\"` for in-page navigation\n- Skip to content link for accessibility\n- Mobile-friendly navigation with hamburger toggle\n\n♿ Accessibility Features\n- Skip link for screen readers\n- Semantic heading structure\n- ARIA labels on interactive elements\n- Descriptive alt text for images\n\n🎨 Design System Integration\n- Google Fonts for Inter and Open Sans\n- Placeholder for `styles.css` and `app.js`\n- Responsive layout with `.container` class\n\n📝 Content Sections\n1. Hero: Headline, subheadline, CTA button\n2. About: Team introduction\n3. Work: Portfolio grid with project highlights\n4. Contact: Comprehensive contact form\n5. Footer: Contact info, social links, copyright\n\nNext steps:\n1. Create `styles.css` to implement design system\n2. Create `app.js` for interactivity\n3. Add actual images and replace placeholders\n\nWould you like me to proceed with creating the CSS and JavaScript files?\n\n### styler\nI have completed the CSS styling for the Forma Studio website. Let me break down the key aspects of the implementation:\n\n🎨 Design System Integration\n- Used design tokens from `design_system.json` for colors, typography, and spacing\n- Implemented CSS custom properties (`:root`) for consistent theming\n- Responsive typography using `clamp()` for fluid scaling\n\n🌐 Responsive Design\n- Mobile-first approach with progressive enhancement\n- Flexbox and CSS Grid for layouts\n- Media queries for tablet and desktop breakpoints\n- Adaptive typography and spacing\n\n♿ Accessibility Features\n- Skip link for screen readers\n- High color contrast\n- Semantic heading structure\n- Focus states for interactive elements\n\n🖌️ Visual Design Highlights\n- Subtle shadows and hover effects\n- Smooth transitions\n- Card and team member hover states\n- Responsive image handling\n\nKey Sections Styled:\n- Navigation\n- Hero\n- About (Team Grid)\n- Portfolio Grid\n- Contact Form\n- Footer\n\nThe CSS is fully validated and matches the HTML structure exactly. The design reflects the modern, minimalist aesthetic defined in the design system.\n\nWould you like me to proceed with creating the JavaScript file or make any adjustments to the CSS?\n\n### interactor\nI've created the `app.js` file for Forma Studio with three core interactive features:\n\n1. 🌊 **Smooth Scrolling Navigation**\n   - Intercepts anchor links with `#` href\n   - Uses `scrollIntoView()` with smooth behavior\n   - Manages focus for accessibility\n   - Prevents default link behavior\n\n2. 📱 **Mobile Menu Toggle**\n   - Toggles `.active` class on navigation\n   - Updates ARIA attributes for screen readers\n   - Changes aria-label dynamically\n   - Manages menu visibility state\n\n3 📝 **Contact Form Validation**\n   - Prevents default form submission\n   - Validates all required fields\n   - Uses regex for email validation\n   - Dynamically creates and removes error messages\n   - Supports screen readers with `role=\"alert\"`\n   - Provides user-friendly feedback\n\nKey Accessibility Features:\n- Semantic focus management\n- ARIA attributes for screen readers\n- Error messages with `role=\"alert\"`\n- Keyboard-friendly interactions\n\nThe JavaScript enhances the user experience while maintaining strong accessibility standards. It follows the semantic structure of the HTML exactly and provides progressive enhancement.\n\nWould you like me to make any adjustments or explain any part of the implementation in more detail?\n\n### integrator\nI have completed the task of creating a 4-page website for Forma Studio. Here's a summary of what I've done:\n\n1. Created 4 separate HTML files:\n   - `home.html`: Landing page with hero section, about teaser, and services\n   - `about.html`: Team and mission page\n   - `work.html`: Portfolio grid showcasing projects\n   - `contact.html`: Contact form and contact information\n\n2. Maintained consistent styling by linking to the same `styles.css`\n\n3. Included the same `app.js` for interactivity across all pages\n\n4. Preserved the design system and content from previous workers\n\n5. Ensured responsive design, semantic HTML, and accessibility features\n\nEach page follows the same structure:\n- Semantic header with navigation\n- Main content sections\n- Footer with contact and social links\n\nThe pages are now ready for further development or deployment. Would you like me to make any specific adjustments or explain any part of the implementation?\n\n### reporter\nI have completed the task of writing a comprehensive report.md that explains the design decisions, visual consistency, responsive implementation, and integration process for the Forma Studio website. The report provides a detailed analysis of how the design system guided the development, how visual consistency was maintained, and the technical strategies used to create a responsive and accessible website.\n\nThe report covers:\n1. Design System Overview (color palette, typography)\n2. Visual Consistency strategies\n3. Responsive Implementation details\n4. Integration Process explanation\n5. Accessibility considerations\n\nIs there anything specific about the report you would like me to elaborate on or modify?\n\n### tester\nI have completed the validation and test report generation for the Forma Studio website. Let me break down the results:\n\n1. HTML Validation (index.html):\n   - Partial Fail: Found an error \"Named entity expected. Got none.\"\n   - This suggests a potential issue with HTML entities or encoding in the index.html file\n   - Recommendation: Review the HTML file for missing or improperly encoded entities\n\n2. CSS Validation (styles.css):\n   - Pass: No CSS syntax errors were found\n   - The CSS file is valid and follows correct syntax\n\n3. JavaScript Validation (app.js):\n   - Pass: No JavaScript syntax errors detected\n   - The JavaScript file contains well-structured, error-handled code\n\n4. File Existence Check:\n   - Confirmed presence of all required files:\n     ✓ index.html\n     ✓ styles.css\n     ✓ app.js\n     ✓ report.md\n\n5. Overall Status: Partial Pass\n   - Most components are valid\n   - Minor HTML validation issue needs attention\n\nI've generated the `test_report.json` file with detailed validation results. The next step would be to address the HTML validation warning, possibly by reviewing the HTML file for any missing HTML entities or encoding issues.\n\nWould you like me to help you resolve the HTML validation warning?\n\n## Files Created\n- design_system.json: {\n- content.txt: [GLOBAL-BRAND-INFO]\n- index.html: <!DOCTYPE html>\n- styles.css: /* Design Tokens & Global Styles */\n- app.js: document.addEventListener('DOMContentLoaded', () => {\n- about.html: <!DOCTYPE html>\n- contact.html: <!DOCTYPE html>\n- home.html: <!DOCTYPE html>\n- work.html: <!DOCTYPE html>\n- report.md: # Forma Studio Website Development Report\n- test_report.json: {\n\n## Dynamic Tools Used\n[\n  \"validate_js\"\n]\n\n## Guidelines\n- Group results by worker\n- Include summary table with worker name, status, and one-liner\n- Mention any dynamic tools that were created and used\n- Reference file paths\n- Keep the report concise\n\nOutput the full Markdown report.", "meta": {}}
